                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/1237: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-22T10:00:00-03:00"
                            >November 22, 1938—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>269. A United Press despatch, dated yesterday, from New York states that
                    Penteado, Financial Attaché to the Brazilian Embassy, has been invited to confer
                    with the Secretary of the Treasury today. The despatch speculates that the
                    conference will deal with the remittance of exchange for exports of American
                    merchandise to Brazil.</p>
                <p>I would greatly appreciate any information the Department can furnish regarding
                    this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
